quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  21,25,"And We did not send before you any messenger but We revealed to him that there is no god but I, so worship Me.""
  21,26,"And they said, "The Rahman (All-Merciful) has taken to Himself a son". Pure is He. They are but servants, honoured."
  21,27,"They do not precede Him in speech and only under His command they act."
  21,28,"He knows what is in front of them and what is behind them, and they make recommendation for none but for whom He likes, and in awe of Him they are apprehensive."
  21,29,"And whoever of them says, "I am god besides Him", is the one whom We will recompense with Jahannam. This is how We recompense the transgressors."
  21,30,"Have the disbelievers not seen that the heavens and the earth were closed, then We opened them? And We created from water every living thing. Would they yet not believe?"
  21,31,"And We created mountains on the earth, lest it should shake with them, and We have made therein paths and ways, so that they are guided."
  21,32,"And We made the sky a roof, protected; and they are averse to its signs."
  21,33,"And He is the One who has created the night and the day, and the sun and the moon, each floating in an orbit."
  21,34,"And We did not assign immortality to any human (even) before you. So, if you die, will they then live forever?"
  21,35,"Everyone has to taste death. And We test you all through bad and good (situations) with a trial. And to Us you are to be returned."